Universal Connector Grid (UCG)

A single standardized physical interface for almost everything

Right now the physical world is full of incompatible connections:
	•	screws
	•	plugs
	•	mounts
	•	brackets
	•	adapters
	•	charging cables
	•	furniture fittings
	•	appliance mounts

Every object has its own proprietary way of attaching to things.

The Universal Connector Grid would be a global mechanical interface standard.

⸻

Core idea

A repeating grid of standardized micro-mount points that can attach anything to anything.

Think of a surface that looks like a subtle matrix of tiny connection nodes.

Example:

• • • • •
• • • • •
• • • • •

Each node could provide:
	•	mechanical attachment
	•	power
	•	data
	•	alignment

⸻

How it works

Objects come with grid-compatible mounts.

Examples:
	•	shelves
	•	lights
	•	electronics
	•	sensors
	•	tools
	•	furniture
	•	robotics modules

Instead of drilling or installing custom brackets, you simply snap into the grid.

⸻

Where the grid lives

The grid could be embedded in:
	•	walls
	•	floors
	•	ceilings
	•	workbenches
	•	vehicles
	•	building frames

Basically structural surfaces.

