⸻

Why this could be civilization-scale

Compare to the shipping container.

Before containers:
	•	every port used different systems
	•	loading cargo was chaotic

After standard containers:
	•	global trade exploded

The container succeeded because of one simple standard.

⸻

UCG could do something similar for the physical world

It would standardize how objects attach and interact.

This would enable:

Modular homes

Walls become infrastructure for attaching things.

Rapid construction

Buildings assembled like large-scale LEGO.

Easy upgrades

Replace components without demolition.

Robotics ecosystems

Robots attach tools and sensors instantly.

Circular economy

Objects reused and reconfigured easily.

⸻

Example chain reaction

Standard grid surfaces → modular objects → universal mounting → faster manufacturing → less waste → easier repair.

⸻

Why it feels obvious after invention

Like paper or the shipping container, the concept is simple:

“What if everything connected to the same grid?”

Once standardized, industries reorganize around it.

⸻

Funny side effect

Once the grid exists, people would start designing entire ecosystems of compatible objects, similar to app stores but for physical components.

